Definition: a bond given to protect the recipient against loss in case the terms of a contract are not filled
Example: a surety company assumes liability for nonperformance
Synonyms: surety_bond, bond, a, given, to, protect, the, recipient, against, loss, in, case, terms, of, contract, are, not, filled, surety, company, assumes, liability, for, nonperformance
Category: noun.possession
